# Internal security documents — describe unfixed vulnerabilities with enough
# detail to exploit them. Kept on disk so the implementing agent can execute
# against them during remediation; the monolith → qrauth-io/qrauth sync
# strips docs/ before pushing to public, so docs/security/ stays private by
# that mechanism too. The /AUDIT*.md pattern protects repo-root audit files
# from syndication because they live outside docs/.
/AUDIT*.md
/docs/security/audit*-remediation-plan.md

# Internal security documents — describe unfixed vulnerabilities with enough
# detail to exploit them. Kept on disk so the implementing agent can execute
# against them during remediation; never committed to the public repo.
# Redacted post-fix retrospectives go into docs/security/remediation-log.md
# once fixes ship.
/AUDIT*.md
/docs/security/audit*-remediation-plan.md
